Interface GrouplikeStructure<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the element of the underlying set.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Structure<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AbelianGroup<T>, CommutativeMonoid<T>, CommutativeSemigroup<T>, Group<T>, Magma<T>, Monoid<T>, Semigroup<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAbelianGroup

    public interface GrouplikeStructure<T>
extends Structure<T>
    Marks a algebraic structure that is of group-like type, aka it has one operation.
